  "prompt": "What are the best restaurants in San Sebastian that won't burn a hole in your pocket?",
  "response": "San Sebastian, known for its exquisite culinary scene, offers plenty of options that won't break the bank. Here are some restaurants that offer great food at affordable prices:\n\n1. **Bar Nestor** - Famous for its juicy steak and tomato salad, this tiny bar is a must-visit. Be sure to arrive early, as it can get quite crowded.\n\n2. **Bodega Donostiarra** - A classic and affordable spot for pintxos (Basque tapas) and raciones (larger portions). Their simple yet delicious dishes are highly popular among locals.\n\n3. **La Cuchara de San Telmo** - Offering creative and delicious pintxos, this place is a favorite among visitors and locals alike. It\u2019s slightly more expensive than typical pintxo bars, but still very reasonable.\n\n4. **Bar Zeruko** - Known for their innovative pintxos, Bar Zeruko is a slightly more upscale option that still offers excellent value for money.\n\n5. **Txepetxa** - Famous for their anchovy pintxos, this small bar is a hidden gem. It's both affordable and delicious, especially if you\u2019re a fan of seafood.\n\n6. **Astelena 1997** - This restaurant offers a great mix of traditional and modern Basque cuisine at affordable prices. The quality of the food is outstanding for the price.\n\n7. **Casa Senra** - A cozy spot with an excellent variety of pintxos and tapas. It\u2019s known for its friendly atmosphere and great value.\n\n8. **Bar Tamboril** \u2013 Situated in the heart of the old town, this bar offers a wide range of affordable and tasty pintxos.\n\nRemember to explore beyond the tourist spots and you\u2019re likely to find even more hidden gems that offer fantastic food at a lower cost. Enjoy your culinary adventures in San Sebastian!",
